{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Jas|2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","chapter":2,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":1,"text":"My brothers and sisters, do not show favoritism as you hold on to the faith in our glorious Lord Jesus Christ.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":2,"text":"For if someone comes into your meeting wearing a gold ring and dressed in fine clothes, and a poor person dressed in filthy clothes also comes in,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":3,"text":"if you look with favor on the one wearing the fine clothes and say, “Sit here in a good place,” and yet you say to the poor person, “Stand over there,” or “Sit here on the floor by my footstool,”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":4,"text":"haven’t you made distinctions among yourselves and become judges with evil thoughts?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":5,"text":"Listen, my dear brothers and sisters: Didn’t God choose the poor in this world to be rich in faith and heirs of the kingdom that he has promised to those who love him?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":6,"text":"Yet you have dishonored the poor. Don’t the rich oppress you and drag you into court?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":7,"text":"Don’t they blaspheme the good name that was invoked over you?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":8,"text":"Indeed, if you fulfill the royal law prescribed in the Scripture, Love your neighbor as yourself, you are doing well.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":9,"text":"If, however, you show favoritism, you commit sin and are convicted by the law as transgressors.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":10,"text":"For whoever keeps the entire law, and yet stumbles at one point, is guilty of breaking it all.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":11,"text":"For he who said, Do not commit adultery, also said, Do not murder. So if you do not commit adultery, but you murder, you are a lawbreaker.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":12,"text":"Speak and act as those who are to be judged by the law of freedom.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":13,"text":"For judgment is without mercy to the one who has not shown mercy. Mercy triumphs over judgment.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":14,"text":"What good is it, my brothers and sisters, if someone claims to have faith but does not have works? Can such faith save him?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":15,"text":"If a brother or sister is without clothes and lacks daily food","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":16,"text":"and one of you says to them, “Go in peace, stay warm, and be well fed,” but you don’t give them what the body needs, what good is it?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":17,"text":"In the same way faith, if it does not have works, is dead by itself.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":18,"text":"But someone will say, “You have faith, and I have works.” Show me your faith without works, and I will show you faith by my works.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":19,"text":"You believe that God is one. Good! Even the demons believe —and they shudder.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":20,"text":"Senseless person! Are you willing to learn that faith without works is useless?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":21,"text":"Wasn’t Abraham our father justified by works in offering Isaac his son on the altar?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":22,"text":"You see that faith was active together with his works, and by works, faith was made complete,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":23,"text":"and the Scripture was fulfilled that says, Abraham believed God, and it was credited to him as righteousness, and he was called God’s friend.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":24,"text":"You see that a person is justified by works and not by faith alone.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":25,"text":"In the same way, wasn’t Rahab the prostitute also justified by works in receiving the messengers and sending them out by a different route?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":2,"verse":26,"text":"For just as the body without the spirit is dead, so also faith without works is dead.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","chapter":2,"paragraphStarts":[1,5,8,12,14,15,18,20],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"The Sin of Favoritism"},{"beforeVerse":14,"text":"Faith and Works"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:2:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"My brothers and sisters, do not show favoritism as you hold on to the faith in our glorious Lord Jesus Christ. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lv 19:15","book":"Lev","chapter":19,"verse":15,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"cross